    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Since browserify exactly copies node's module resolution algorithm, you can put things in `node_modules`. Just symlink the stuff in `components` into `node_modules` and you can `require()` it. Or if you symlink the whole components directory into `node_modules/` then you can do `require('components/NAME')` like you suggest. When you install packages with npm it will helpfully install the packages into `node_modules/` so you won't need to do anything extra.\n\nhttp://stackoverflow.com/questions/15313720/nodejs-local-modules-for-complex-application-structures\n",
